<subSubSection id="4DE7B10A4490D29F5F4C093135053198" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="description">
<paragraph id="40E58F616BF3222E83F07DDD11105490" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D254E4C7B85371F4B57E8A66312A83A7" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Perennial liana, stems woody, floccose. Leaves often absent at anthesis, shortly petiolate, 3.5-11 
<normalizedToken id="5B2F41AB9837C1C1D1C8FBD0C16A0617" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
1-4 cm, thick in texture, oblong or obovate-oblanceolate, apex cuneate and with prominent stout mucro, base narrowly cuneate, densely tomentose on both surfaces, grey adaxially, white abaxially; petioles 8-20 mm, white-tomentose. Inflorescence on short leafy axillary branchlets 2-8 cm long; bracteoles 5-6 mm, linear-oblanceolate, tomentose, caducous; pedicels 5-14 mm, pilose to tomentose; sepals subequal, 10-11 
<normalizedToken id="C84E9730B66A2EA2AB30B0C1919DA767" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
6-7 mm, elliptic, obtuse, densely tomentose; corolla 3.5-4.5 cm long, hypocrateriform, basal cylindrical tube 3-3.5 
<normalizedToken id="868D24A6958CF68E92EDE4B00DBA78AD" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.5-0.6 cm, dark red, limb, 1.5-2 cm diam., red, glabrous, stamens exserted.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
